#-------------------------------------------------------------------------------
#-------------------------------------------------------------------------------
# NotesBootServerPXE.
#-------------------------------------------------------------------------------
#-------------------------------------------------------------------------------
You need to get PXELINUX.

Look up 
	"http://syslinux.zytor.com/pxe.php"
and 
	"http://syslinux.zytor.com/faq.php"

to read up and get the latest downloads.

Untar syslinux

	tar -xvf syslinux-2.08.tar

As root create a /tftpboot direcitory with the proper ownership and accesses.

	su root
	cd /
	mkdir tftpboot
	chown nobody:nobody /tftpboot -R
	chmod ugo+wrx /tftpboot

Copy the pxelinux.0 file to the /tftpboot directory

	cp syslinux-2.08/pxelinux.0 /tftpboot

Create a pxe configuration directory

	mkdir /tftpboot/pxelinux.cfg


